title: The Oatmeal of Christian Practice
description:
Joseph grew up very Catholic. He's of Italian and Mexican heritage. Went to a Jesuit HS and then into the California UC system. He was a history major but built up student debt so had to go into manufacturing like his father. The faith wasn't his young and he went full materialist atheist in college. Via Jordan Peterson he began to reconsider. He's a very thoughtful, reflective man and so we talk.

Italian sycilian mexican
Raised very Catholic
Loyola HS in LA
Hughes and Boeing
Academic to manufacturing environment
Satellite production
Latent hostility to Christianity
Stalinist purges
Heavy metal fan

Jordan Peterson
Align how I act with what I consume and what i say I believe
Hold those reactions in check
Strong sense of prudence and caution
Align towards a Christian orientation
Oatmeal of Christian practice
Predestination
